<TITLE> Intel chief launches 'World Ahead Programme' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 4 (bdnews24.com) - Intel Corporation's chief Craig Barrett arrived in Dhaka Tuesday to inaugurate the "World Ahead Programme" in his capacity as chairman of the Global Alliance for Information Technologies. The programme's aim is to increase the uptake of high-speed information technology in the developing world. Intel Corporation will work in conjunction with the Bangladesh government and Grameen Solutions to spread the new technology. Barrett said: "Dr Muhammad Yunus (chairman of Grameen Solutions) has already proved how much change this kind of programme can bring to the country by creating opportunities." This kind of programme could play a role in the socio-economic development of poor countries in the 21st century, he added. Barrett launched the programme at Radisson Water Garden Hotel and later met chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed in his whirlwind half-day visit. bdnews24.
